Crambus sperryellus is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Alexander Barrett Klots in 1940. It is found in the US states of California and adjacent Arizona.
The length of the forewings is 11â€“14 mm. The ground color of the forewings is bright golden brown, darker along the costal margin and along the dorsal edge of the silvery-white stripe. The hindwings are pale brownish white, darker apically and terminally.